jibe.sdk.client
Class JibeIntents

java.lang.Object
  jibe.sdk.client.JibeIntents

public class JibeIntents
extends java.lang.Object

Defines the Intents that are generated by the Jibe Realtime Engine. Clients should register to receive any Jibe Services Intents that they will use.

Field Detail

ACTION_INCOMING_CHAT_MESSAGE

public static final java.lang.String ACTION_INCOMING_CHAT_MESSAGE
An Intent representing an incoming chat-message. If this Intent is issued via an RCS community, it represents a sessionless SIP Page Mode Instant Message. This Intent has the following extras:

String EXTRA_TEXT, the text of the message.
Long EXTRA_RAWCONTACTID, the sender's raw contact ID, if sender is a known contact - otherwise it may be null .
String EXTRA_USERID, the sender's user ID, which is normally an MSISDN.

See Also:
ChatSessionService, Constant Field Values

ACTION_INCOMING_VIDEOSHARE

public static final java.lang.String ACTION_INCOMING_VIDEOSHARE
An Intent representing an incoming one-way video share. This Intent contains the following extras:

String EXTRA_SESSION_ID, a unique ID for the chat session.
Long EXTRA_RAWCONTACTID, the sender's raw contact ID, if the sender is a known contact - otherwise it may be null .
String EXTRA_USERID, the sender's user ID (which is normally an MSISDN).
String EXTRA_USERURI, the sender's full SIP URI.
String EXTRA_WIDTH, the width of the incoming video.
String EXTRA_HEIGHT, the height of the incoming video.
String EXTRA_CODEC, the codec of the incoming video.
String EXTRA_FRAMERATE, the frame rate of the incoming video.
String EXTRA_ORIENTATION, the orientation of the incoming video ("landscape" / "portrait").

See Also:
VideoSharingService, Constant Field Values

ACTION_INCOMING_FILETRANSFER

public static final java.lang.String ACTION_INCOMING_FILETRANSFER
An Intent representing an incoming file-transfer. This Intent contains the following extras:

String EXTRA_SESSION_ID, the unique ID for the file transfer session.
Long EXTRA_FILENAME, the name of the incoming file.
Long EXTRA_URL, the path to the file.
Long EXTRA_SIZE, the size (in bytes) of the incoming file.
String EXTRA_USERID, the sender's user ID (which is normally an MSISDN).
String EXTRA_USERURI, the sender's full SIP URI.
Long EXTRA_RAWCONTACTID, the sender's raw contact ID, if the sender is a known contact - otherwise it may be null .

See Also:
FileTransferService, Constant Field Values

ACTION_OPEN_FILETRANSFER

public static final java.lang.String ACTION_OPEN_FILETRANSFER
An Intent used to open a file-transfer. Applications should filter for this Intent, in order to react to clicks in the Android notification bar during a file transfer. This Intent contains the following extras:

String EXTRA_SESSION_ID, the unique ID for the file transfer session.
Long EXTRA_FILENAME, the name of the incoming file.
Long EXTRA_URL, the path to the file.
Long EXTRA_SIZE, the size (in bytes) of the incoming file.
String EXTRA_USERID, the sender's user ID (which is normally an MSISDN).
String EXTRA_USERURI, the sender's full SIP URI.
Long EXTRA_RAWCONTACTID, the sender's raw contact ID, if the sender is a known contact - otherwise it may be null .

See Also:
FileTransferService, Constant Field Values

ACTION_INCOMING_DATASESSION

public static final java.lang.String ACTION_INCOMING_DATASESSION
An Intent representing an incoming data-session. This Intent contains the following extras:

String EXTRA_SESSION_ID, a unique ID for the data session.
String EXTRA_USERID, the sender's user ID (which is normally an MSISDN).
String EXTRA_USERURI, the sender's full SIP URI.
String EXTRA_DISPLAYNAME, the sender's display name, if available.
String EXTRA_SUBJECT, invitation's subject, if available.
Long EXTRA_RAWCONTACTID, the sender's raw contact ID, if the sender is a known contact - otherwise it may be null .

See Also:
DataSessionService, Constant Field Values

ACTION_INCOMING_CALL

public static final java.lang.String ACTION_INCOMING_CALL
An Intent representing an incoming VoIP-call which can be audio only or audio+video. This Intent contains the following extras:

String EXTRA_SESSION_ID, a unique ID for the voice call.
String EXTRA_USERID, the sender's user ID (which is normally an MSISDN).
String EXTRA_USERURI, the sender's full SIP URI.
Long EXTRA_RAWCONTACTID, the sender's raw contact ID, if the sender is a known
int EXTRA_MEDIA_INFO, information on the media the sender proposes for the call contact - otherwise it may be null .

See Also:
CallService, Constant Field Values

ACTION_INCOMING_CHATSESSION

public static final java.lang.String ACTION_INCOMING_CHATSESSION
An Intent representing an incoming chat-session. When issued through the RCS community, it represents a request to join an MSRP chat session. This Intent contains the following extras:

String EXTRA_TEXT, the text of the chat session's first message.
String EXTRA_SESSION_ID, the unique ID for the chat session.
Long EXTRA_RAWCONTACTID, the sender's raw contact ID, if the sender is a known contact - otherwise it may be null .
String EXTRA_USERID, the sender's user ID (which is normally an MSISDN).
String EXTRA_USERURI, the sender's full SIP URI.

See Also:
ChatSessionService, Constant Field Values

ACTION_ARENA_CHALLENGE

public static final java.lang.String ACTION_ARENA_CHALLENGE
An Intent received when challenging a user from the Arena UI. The receiving application will typically start a gaming session when receiving with the remote user identified via the intent extras. This intent will contain the following extras:
  • Long EXTRA_JIBE_USER_ID, the arena id of the remote user
  • String EXTRA_DISPLAYNAME, the nickname of the remote user
  • String EXTRA_USERID, the remote users user ID (which is normally an MSISDN)
  • String EXTRA_SUBJECT, the message which should be send together the challenge

See Also:
Constant Field Values

ACTION_ARENA_SHOW_FRIENDS

public static final java.lang.String ACTION_ARENA_SHOW_FRIENDS
An Intent to launch Jibe Arena's friends list activity If a version of the Jibe Arena that supports the friends list is not installed a ActivityNotFoundException is thrown This Intent can contain the following extras:

String EXTRA_APPLICATION_ID, filters friends by this application id

EXTRA_APPLICATION_ID

public static final java.lang.String EXTRA_APPLICATION_ID
A string, representing the application id of a Jibe A2A enabled application. Used for launching Arena activities from an A2A enabled app directly into a view filtered by that application. This extra is used in the following intents: jibe.sdk.client.internal.PrivateJibeIntents#ACTION_ARENA_SHOW_FRIENDS
